{"title":"`city_any_dataset()`","markdown":{"headingText":"`city_any_dataset()`","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n## Introduction\n\n`city_any_dataset()` serves as a fallback when a dataset cannot be located through `city_list_datasets()`. Rather than searching the package's metadata catalog, this function downloads data directly from a Socrata JSON endpoint.\n\n```{mermaid}\nflowchart TD\nA[User provides JSON endpoint] --> B[Validate URL]\nB --> C[Send API request]\nC --> D[Download JSON]\nD --> E[Post-process data]\nE --> F[Return tibble]\n```\n\nIn most cases, users should prefer `city_pull_dataset()`, since it provides readable dataset keys and additional convenience features. However, `city_any_dataset()` is useful for newly published datasets, datasets omitted from the metadata catalog, or any valid Socrata JSON endpoint.\n\n::: callout-tip\n## When should I use `city_any_dataset()`?\n\nUse `city_pull_dataset()` whenever the dataset is available in the package catalog.\n\nUse `city_any_dataset()` only when you already have a Socrata JSON endpoint or when the dataset is not available through `city_list_datasets()`.\n:::\n\n## What Needs to Change\n\nVery little of the underlying function changes from city to city.\n\nThe primary customizations are:\n\n- updating package-specific function names\n- updating package-specific internal helper names\n- replacing the example Socrata domain\n- replacing the example dataset UID\n\n## Verifying Your Results\n\nAfter making the necessary replacements, verify that:\n\n- [ ] a valid JSON endpoint downloads successfully\n- [ ] invalid URLs produce informative errors\n- [ ] column names are cleaned when `clean_names = TRUE`\n- [ ] type coercion behaves as expected\n- [ ] documentation examples execute successfully\n\n## Template Values to Replace\n\nBelow is a table on the template values that need to be replaced per the specific city, and what they need to be replaced with.\n\n| Template value | Replace with |\n|------------------------|------------------------------------------------|\n| `CITY_NAME` | Full city name, such as `NYC`, `Chicago`, or `Los Angeles` |\n| `city_any_dataset()` | Package-specific public function name |\n| `city_list_datasets()` | Package-specific catalog-listing function |\n| `city_pull_dataset()` | Package-specific catalog-based download function |\n| `.city_validate_limit()` | Package-specific internal prefix |\n| `.city_validate_timeout()` | Package-specific internal prefix |\n| `.city_get_json()` | Package-specific internal prefix |\n| `.city_postprocess()` | Package-specific internal prefix |\n| `SOCRATA_DOMAIN` | The city portal’s Socrata domain |\n| `\"abcd-1234\"` | A real example Socrata dataset UID |\n| Example dataset description | The name or description of the dataset associated with the example UID |\n\n## Common Pitfalls\n\nWhen customizing `city_any_dataset()`, the most common issues are:\n\n- Forgetting to replace `SOCRATA_DOMAIN` in the documentation examples.\n- Using a dataset page URL instead of the JSON endpoint.\n- Forgetting the `.json` suffix on the endpoint.\n- Using a dataset UID that no longer exists.\n- Updating the function but forgetting to update the documentation examples.\n- Assuming every Socrata endpoint is included in the package catalog.\n\n## Chapter Checklist\n\nBefore continuing, confirm that you have:\n\n- [ ] Updated all package function prefixes.\n- [ ] Updated all internal helper prefixes.\n- [ ] Replaced the example Socrata domain.\n- [ ] Replaced the example dataset UID.\n- [ ] Verified the example JSON endpoint downloads successfully.\n- [ ] Verified `clean_names = TRUE` works.\n- [ ] Verified `coerce_types = TRUE` works.\n- [ ] Verified the documentation examples run successfully.\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":fal